x^2+1 - x^2
\dfrac1{x(x^2+1)} = \dfrac{x^2+1-x^2}{x(x^2+1)} = \dfrac{x^2+1}{x(x^2+1)} - \dfrac{x^2}{x(x^2+1)} = \dfrac1x - \dfrac{x}{x^2+1}
\int \dfrac{dx}{x(x^2+1)} = \int \dfrac{dx}x - \int\dfrac{x}{x^2+1}dx = \log(x) - \dfrac12 \log(x^2+1) + \text{ constant}
\displaystyle \frac{1}{x(x^2 + 1)} = \frac{1 + x^2 - x^2}{x(x^2 + 1)}
